RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 58. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. MERGER OF EQUALS was bumped leaving the gate and rounded the first turn in the three path, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn in the three path and flattened in the lane. BOCA BIRDIE saved ground well off the pace, bid nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path, eased out entering the stretch and passed rivals before flattening strid. PRETTY SPECTACULAR rated just off the pace and off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase from the half mile pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened in the lane. SHESAHUMBLEHUSTLER was bumped outward and into Merger Of Equals leaving the gate, raced well off the pace and never factored. OJITOS BELLOS rounded the opening turn in the four path, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but flattened in the three path of the far turn. MODELO RUBIA ducked out and made contact with Shesahumblehustler leaving the gate, rounded the first turn in the five path, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole but gave way into the far turn.

IRISH FIRE entered the first turn in the five path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded through the backstretch.
